        "client_msg_id": "1957609A-EEFB-4B2D-B504-1D3C8628D217",
        "text": "I think this default behaviour might be surprising behaviour to most. I think order controls in flumine in general can be a little surprising (selection exposure is not related to P&amp;L, only net exposure of trades on that selection, correct?), and in live trading these surprises could get expensive. I think defaults could defer to risk minimisation and that might make more sense: a dead bot that crashed out due to an exception can’t win big, but it also critically can’t lose big either. You can’t say that about a faulty live one…",
