    {
        "user": "U02RN7YDRQ9",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1710174927.553839",
        "client_msg_id": "f4c86fe8-6247-4255-8911-7bf26e0b786d",
        "text": "I think <@U012XF5CNPN> explains it well and encapsulates the reasons I have turned the \"feature\" off. There are a mass of issues that can cause Python to throw concrete excpetions and they are not just related to Python, flumine or flumine strategy code. They include exceptions from the operating system and bugs in any of the host of python packages used - all of which would be ignored by flumine. Imho the probability of an exception arising is real and I favour the dead bot theory rather than the faulty live one.",
